# Code Documentation


## When to update

- New file → full file header
- Changed behavior on **exported** class, function, type, or interface → update its JSDoc
- New or changed **multi-step** logic inside a function → add or refresh **inline step comments**
- Major rewrite of file purpose → refresh prose + `@date`
- Do **not** add JSDoc on every private helper — use inline step comments inside the body instead (see below)

## Path comment (line 1)

| Location | Required |
|----------|----------|
| `public/scripts/**` | Yes — `// public/scripts/.../filename.ts` |
| `src/**` | Optional — `// src/.../filename.ts` when helpful |

Imports follow immediately after the header block.

## File header block

Every `.ts` source file opens with:

```typescript
/**
 * ClassOrTopic — one-line title
 *
 * 2–3 sentences: responsibilities, key dependencies, layer boundary
 * (e.g. business logic vs HTTP, façade vs delegate).
 *
 * @author: @gatahcha
 * @date: YYYY-MM-DD
 * @version: 1.0.0
 * @description: Short index line — what this file owns.
 */
```

<!-- @rdschrs: Added contributor-safe authorship guidance for feature-owned files. -->

| Tag | Rule |
|-----|------|
| `@author` | `@gatahcha`, `@rdschrs`, or `EngE-AI Team` — use the actual file owner and preserve existing attribution |
| `@date` | Creation date; update on major rewrite only |
| `@version` | Version number; update on major rewrite only |
| `@description` | One concise line; may wrap — not a duplicate of the title |

**Prefer** title + prose body (as in `rag-app.ts`). Filename-only first line (as in `enge-ai-mongodb.ts`) is acceptable for thin modules.

## Class JSDoc

After exports, document the class when it is the file’s main export:

```typescript
/**
 * EngEAI_MongoDB
 *
 * Thin singleton connecting to MongoDB and delegating to domain modules.
 * Public method names preserved for callers.
 */
```

List responsibilities in prose — do not enumerate every method in the class block unless the class is a façade catalog.

## Function and method JSDoc

**Exported and public methods** — required. **Private** — only when non-obvious.

### Preferred shape (behavior first)

Use for anything with side effects, filters, or domain rules — see `retrieveForChat` in `rag-app.ts`:

```typescript
/**
 * {functionName} - {description}
 *
 * @param query - Student message text used for vector search
 * @param courseName - Course display name for Qdrant filter
 * @param options - Optional limit and score threshold overrides
 * @returns Retrieved chunks; empty array when skipped or unavailable
 * @throws Error when RAGApp failed to initialize (hard failures only)
 */
```

### Minimal shape (simple accessors)

Acceptable for thin getters/singleton accessors — see `getInstance`, `getRagModule`:

```typescript
/**
 * getInstance — returns the singleton RAGApp instance
 *
 * @returns Initialized RAGApp
 * @throws Error if initialization fails
 */
```

### Avoid

- Restating the obvious from the signature (`@param config - The configuration`)
- `@returns void` on constructors
- `{name} - Constructor for the X class` with no behavioral note
- JSDoc on string-literal prompt constants (see `prompt-engineer/01-conversation-modes-docs.mdc`)

## Inline step comments (logical pipeline)

**Required** inside functions that have a sequence of non-obvious steps — upload/parse flows, I/O, branching pipelines, multi-phase business logic. This is how the next developer reads the *story* of the method without spelunking every line.

Reference: `parseDocument` and `uploadDocument` in `src/rag/rag-app.ts`.

### Pattern

One `//` comment **immediately before** each logical step — validate, prepare, branch, act, cleanup:

```typescript
// Validate the file extension
const documentFileName = input.file.originalname || '';
const fileExtension = documentFileName.split('.').pop()?.toLowerCase();

// If the file extension is not supported, throw an error
if (!fileExtension || !supportedExtensions.includes(fileExtension)) {
    throw new Error(`Unsupported file type: ...`);
}

// Create a temporary directory if it doesn't exist
const tempDir = path.join(__dirname, '..', 'tempfiles');
if (!fs.existsSync(tempDir)) {
    fs.mkdirSync(tempDir, { recursive: true });
}

// Create a temporary file name
const tempFileName = `${Date.now()}-${documentFileName}`;

// Write the file to the temporary directory
try {
    fs.writeFileSync(filePath, buffer);

    // If the file extension is txt, read the file and return the extracted text
    if (fileExtension === 'txt') { ... }

    // If the file extension is not txt, parse the file and return the extracted text
    const parseResult = await this.documentParser.parse({ filePath }, 'text');
} finally { ... }
```

### Rules

| Do | Don't |
|----|-------|
| Comment each **logical step** (validate → prepare → branch → act → cleanup) | Comment every single line |
| Use a full sentence: what this step accomplishes in the pipeline | Repeat the code (`// increment i`) |
| Comment **branch intent**: why this path vs the other | Leave long `try`/`finally` or I/O blocks uncommented |
| Keep step comments when you change the flow | Use `// DEBUG:` / `// TEMP:` as permanent docs |

**JSDoc** = what the function promises (contract). **Step comments** = how the body achieves it (procedure). Both belong on non-trivial methods.

### When step comments are optional

- One-liner delegates and trivial getters
- Self-explanatory glue already named by extracted helpers (`const published = filterPublished(items)`)

## Interfaces and types

Reference: `src/types/shared.ts` — synced manually with `public/scripts/types.ts` (no cross-import).

### Interface / type block (when and why)

Every **exported** interface or type gets a JSDoc block **above** the declaration explaining:

- **When** it is used — persistence, API response, monitor UI, chat pipeline, etc.
- **Why** it exists — domain role, boundary (e.g. not persisted vs Mongo canonical), link to related types

```typescript
/** One cell in the course-summary / monitor stacked bar chart. */
export interface CourseSummaryStackedBarValue { ... }

/**
 * Per-user memory-agent record stored in Mongo.
 *
 * Used when loading struggle labels for Socratic chat injection. Updated by the
 * memory agent after repeated difficulty — not copied onto {@link Chat}.
 */
export interface MemoryAgentEntry { ... }
```

For complex domains, a short prose block before the interface (see struggle-topic types above `MemoryAgentChapterStruggle` in `shared.ts`) is encouraged.

### Property justification (same line)

On shared cross-module interfaces (`shared.ts`, FE mirror types), each property gets a **trailing `//` comment on the same line** — the justification for that field:

```typescript
export interface CourseSummaryStackedBarValue {
    categoryId: string; // stacked-bar segment id for chart legend lookup
    studentCount: number; // headcount in this segment for the bar height
    tooltip: string; // hover text in monitor course-summary chart
}
```

| Do | Don't |
|----|-------|
| Explain **why the field exists** or **how it is consumed** | Restate the property name only (`// the user id`) |
| Keep trailing comments when adding or changing a property | Leave shared interface properties bare |
| Use `/** */` on a property only when justification needs 2+ lines | Duplicate the same text in both `/** */` and `//` |

Type aliases and unions: one-line JSDoc above with when/why. Enums: comment non-obvious members inline.

## Domain overrides

| Area | Also follow |
|------|-------------|
| `src/chat/conversation-modes/**` | `prompt-engineer/01-conversation-modes-docs.mdc` |
| `src/db/mongo/**` | File header + JSDoc on exports; idempotency in `@description` or prose |

## Check-in

Developer confirms documentation before considering the **Document** phase complete.
